<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Tallow" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Tallow,</orth> the grease or fat of an animal: <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. V, 5, 16</bibl> (a phrase properly applied to bucks growing lean after rutting-time). <bibl n="shak. err 3.2.100" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 2, 100</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.125" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 125</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.2.179" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 2, 179</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.5.158" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 5, 158</bibl> (<emph>t. face,</emph> i. e. pale face). <bibl n="shak. cym 1.6.110" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 6, 110</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>